{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4f2b10fc-32b9-48de-8f75-2f2167f5c5a5","content":"**Starting with MSTest.Sdk 4.0.0, VSTest support is disabled by default.**\n\nThe MSTest SDK now uses **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** as the sole runner. The VSTest compatibility layer (`Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild` adapter) is no longer included unless you opt in, so `vstest.console` can't discover your tests.\n\n### Fix — pick one:\n\n**Option A: Re-enable VSTest compatibility** (quick CI fix)\n\nAdd this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**Option B (recommended): Switch your CI to the new runner**\n\nReplace `vstest.console` with:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test          # works out of the box\n# or run the test exe directly:\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj -- --list-tests\n```\n\nThe new platform is faster and doesn't need vstest.console at all. Option B is the intended path forward.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3e82422d-93ef-4070-9754-3dc34d617079","outputTokens":263,"requestId":"67C7:163FFF:1C6CE00:2010FE0:69FD5483"},"id":"3cf331f6-61b3-449b-8980-63e4debf9aac","timestamp":"2026-05-08T03:12:10.733Z","parentId":"ffe21f8e-8966-4690-a1a7-a61946240958"}
